You already have an incredible, production-grade foundation. For a Capstone Project in an **Agentic AI Bootcamp**, the goal is to show off the autonomy, reasoning, and multi-modal capabilities of the agents. 

To take this from "A+" to an absolute **"Show-Stopper"**, here are three "badass" features you could add to blow the judges away:

### 1. The "Live Crisis" Auto-Trigger (True Autonomy)
Right now, the human has to move sliders to see what happens. 
**The Badass Level:** Create a "Live Simulation" mode. Time ticks forward automatically on the dashboard, and a background script injects random "Crises" (e.g., a sudden 5-car pileup, or a flu outbreak). The XGBoost model is constantly polling this live data in the background. When wait times spike into the "Critical" zone, the dashboard flashes red, and the Agents **proactively** wake up, solve the shortage, and send an alert to the screen: *"CRISIS DETECTED: We have formulated an emergency staffing plan. Review immediately."*

### 2. "Chief Nursing Officer" Interrogation Chat (Agentic Reasoning)
Right now, the human just clicks "Approve" or "Reject".
**The Badass Level:** Replace the simple approval buttons with an interactive chat window linked to a "Chief Nursing Officer (CNO)" Agent. Before approving, the human can interrogate the system. 
* *Human:* "Why did you pick Nurse A instead of Nurse B? She's cheaper." 
* *CNO Agent:* "I understand she is cheaper, but the Patient Safety Agent vetoed Nurse B because she lacks ICU certifications, and our XGBoost model shows a severe critical patient load."
This shows the judges that your agents aren't just running scripts—they can dynamically defend their reasoning!

### 3. Multi-Modal "Code Blue" Voice Overrides (Multi-Modal AI)
**The Badass Level:** Add a microphone button or audio upload feature to the dashboard. A hospital administrator can upload an audio file or type: *"We just got a call from dispatch. Massive chemical spill downtown, expect 20 critical patients in 10 minutes."*
An Agent listens to the audio, extracts the clinical urgency, automatically overrides the dashboard sliders, forces the XGBoost model to recalculate, and the Financial/Safety agents immediately scramble to draft an "All-Hands" crisis roster. 

Any **one** of these three would make for a phenomenal capstone presentation. Which one sounds like the most fun to build?